OL,3,CChief Constable retires amid
OL,4,Cinvestigation into alleged gross
OL,5,Cmisconduct
OL,7,F"The serving of a gross misconduct
OL,8,Fnotice does not mean that disciplinary
OL,9,Fproceedings will necessarily follow.
OL,10,FAt the end of our investigation, we
OL,11,Fwill decide whether Mr Chilton should
OL,12,Fface disciplinary proceedings. No
OL,13,Fcriminal offences have currently been
OL,14,Fidentified as part of our ongoing
OL,15,Finvestigation."
